s: 16<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/2/02 5:45:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://membres.lycos.fr/thegreatvahn/gekiganger_11.jpeg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What spec is best for a skald?</span><hr size=1> If you dont like hammer i suggest you take axe,sword style are not appropriate to most situation. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/utyris.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tyris</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.animatedgif.net/flags/flagsusa/usa_gs_e0.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/2/02 11:28:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://wolvesofwar.homestead.com/files/designpix/skull2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What spec is best for a skald?</span><hr size=1> ahh ok thanks for the input. i probably will respec when given an opertunity but i will wait till the do the styles revamp and since im level 33 i think i got time to wait till 50. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ujaliawolfsdottir.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jalia Wolfsdottir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/3/02 7:51:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What spec is best for a skald?</span><hr size=1> Hi Tyris!<br><br>Another thing to think about is that apparently, some of the Albies &quot;epic&quot; armours have bonuses to crush resistance as part of their magical endowments. So you may be getting a much smaller bonus than you think when all that extra resistance is added up. <p><hr align=left width=255><table><tr><td width=125>Rilee MacLear<br>Skald of Siol Lear<br></td><td  width=125 align=right>Jalia MacLear<br>Healer of Siol Lear<br></td></tr><tr><td colspan=2 align=center><i>Midgard &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Percival</i></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugelainsidhe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gelain Sidhe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/3/02 8:03:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What spec is best for a skald?</span><hr size=1> And the other thing Tyris ... I really don't think there is such a huge difference in the weapons to overly worry, so playing on an RP server, go with whatever seems best to you from an RP stand point. I had a quick look at the styles from each weapon and then chose the one that felt right to me: AXE <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src=http://home.cox.rr.com/junix/DAoCpics/Gelain25.jpg></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uwarpfield.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WarpField</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.galia.org/hoodednomads/DAoC/images/emblem/emblem_midgard_thedethguild.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/7/02 10:59:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=9.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.galia.org/hoodednomads/DAoC/images/emblem/emblem_midgard_thedethguild.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What spec is best for a skald?</span><hr size=1> You will likely not be spec'ing the weapon much beyond 44 anyway. The differences between the weapons is so slight, that you will not gimp your character by picking one weapon over the other. My Skald uses a player crafted 2H Mithral Dwarven Great Sword that I am very happy with. If I had the chance to reroll him, I would still choose the sword. <br><br>Unlike my Berzerker, my Skald doesn't rely as heavily on those 2 &amp; 3 style chains. Most of the time I just use the Assault style with the Draw Out, (taunt), and Temper, (detaunt), styles when required. I do just fine against even con Albs wearing plate armor. That plate armor avails them naught against my DD's. There's nothing quite like the sound of an Alb screaming in pain through that plate armor when I shout my warcries at him. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><b>__________________________________________<br><ul><li>Muddy Waters - 34 Berzerker</li><br>(Level 376+ Weaponcraft)<br><li>Orobolis - 35 Skald</li><br>(Level 400+ Armorcraft)<li>WarpField Starlighter - 10 Runemaster</li><li>Bitwise Operator - 10 Shaman</li><li>Warpfield - Future Paladin(Nimue, Albion)</li